narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: 2 presentations on current research in decision theory, ambiguity, etc. Very interesting for students with a psychology/math background.2 professors that add comments and listen to our talks.class consists of like 20 or so econ/math or math majors...everyone literally has worked in finance hahahaha so expect conversations and tie-ins to the industry/investing.
Well Econ& Math has to. But it is a very good course nonetheless - very high enjoyment/learning:effort ratio.
A great relaxing course to cover multiple topics and learn about different subjects in a broad manner.
